Description: Body sherd of Attic black-figured pottery closed vessel, possibly an amphora; exterior: from top, part of two vertical strokes; two narrow dilute bands; black-figure decoration consisting of frontal head of panther with nose and forehead in added red.
Bibliographic references: Venit 1982 / Painted Pottery from the Greek Mainland found in Egypt, 640-450 BC (p 461, no. B781)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0052) (Phase 1)
